The paper proposes a novel approach for anomaly detection in High Performance Computing systems based on a Machine (Deep) Learning technique, namely a type of neural network called autoencoder. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper deals with anomaly detection, which is a common topic in the Cybersecurity (cs.CR) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) categories. The paper also deals with High Performance Computing systems, which suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NE, and cs.SY, in that order.
